#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
gemma-ui — Unified Terminal UI for the Bazzite Local AI Operations Stack

A single entry point that routes to all Gemma helpers and security tools.
Each mode delegates to existing helpers instead of duplicating logic.

Usage:
    gemma-ui                              # Interactive mode selector
    gemma-ui --mode general               # Start in general chat mode
    gemma-ui --mode security              # Start in security tool mode
    gemma-ui --mode memory                # Start in memory search mode
    gemma-ui --mode repo                  # Start in repo brief mode
    gemma-ui --mode reports               # Show recent reports
    gemma-ui --mode health                # Run safe health checks
    gemma-ui --demo-ui                   # Render demo without running tools
    gemma-ui --demo-layout               # Render polished layout mockup (no tools)
    gemma-ui --tui                       # Launch curses persistent TUI prototype
    gemma-ui --list-modes                 # List available modes
    gemma-ui --help                       # Show help

Modes:
    [1] general    Normal local Gemma chat (gemma-bazzite)
    [2] security   Security tool console (gemma-security-chat)
    [3] memory     RuVector/Stage 3A memory search
    [4] repo       Repo commands for gem and bazzite-laptop
    [5] voice      Voice mode (setup/explain)
    [6] reports    Show recent generated reports
    [7] health     Safe health/status checks

UI Commands:
    /help       Show help
    /mode       Show mode selector
    /clear      Clear the screen
    /save       Save current session state
    /quit       Exit

Safety:
    - Advisory only. No autonomous actions.
    - No sudo without explicit user confirmation.
    - Missing helpers shown as "not configured" rather than failing.
    - Delegates to existing helpers; does not replace them.

Canonical Paths:
    - Scripts:     ~/.local/bin/
    - Config:      ~/.config/bazzite-security/gemma-ui.json
    - Logs:        ~/.local/state/bazzite-security/logs/
    - Reports:     ~/offload/security-reports/manual/
    - Cache:       ~/.cache/bazzite-security/
"""

